name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
A poster posted the contents of the Constitution one by one in Baidu Tieba to test how many articles of the Constitution can be displayed in Baidu Tieba.
However, the embarrassing thing is that, apart from the titles of each chapter, only about 10 articles of the Constitution out of the 136 articles that the poster has posted so far can be seen by the public, and the vast majority of the remaining articles of the Constitution are automatically blocked by the system. (Multiple pictures)

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
On May 1, the Chinese Embassy in Canada criticized Canadian Prime Minister Trudeau for his inappropriate remarks regarding China.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Netizens submitted articles saying that they have recently received official media pushes on how to prevent circumvention of the firewall. The articles focus on not downloading, not registering, and not using foreign software such as YouTube, Facebook, Twitter, and potato. The end of the article even mentions how to self-check whether there are related circumvention software and behaviors in the phone using Huawei mate30 as an example.

On May 1, at Jiefangbei in Chongqing, someone threw flyers on the street.
The specific reason is unknown at present, but judging from the content of the flyers, it is suspected to be related to the suspension of pension payments.

name: 李老师不是你老师

On the morning of May 1, a fire broke out at a chemical plant in Liaocheng, Shandong. The accident caused 5 deaths and 1 injury. The cause of the accident is still under investigation.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizens added that in March 2021, the person suspected of throwing leaflets made similar remarks on Weibo. 
Apparently, the long period of time without a solution to the problem became the reason why he finally did this at Jiefangbei.
